  "summary": "Malicious code in hooktest1 (PyPI)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: kam193 (b3e91d71ab21e3575f1354593a314d50bc188b0db7b3851040e522426a765417)\nDuring installation, the package starts a code to retrieve and execute commands from Discord\n\n\n---\n\nCategory: MALICIOUS - The campaign has clearly malicious intent, like infostealers.\n\n\nCampaign: 2025-11-hooktest1\n\n\nReasons (based on the campaign):\n\n\n - The package overrides the install command in setup.py to execute malicious code during installation.\n\n\n - The package contains code to execute remote commands (probably limited to a specific set) on the victim's machine.\n\n\n - rat\n",
